HEADWORD: calciferol
<hw>cal*cif"er*ol</hw> <pr>(k⟦acr⟧l*s⟦icr⟧f"⟦etil⟧r*⟦add⟧l)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <def>One of the forms of <er>vitamin D</er>, a fat-soluble
vitamin that prevents rickets. It is an unsaturated alcohol
(<chform>C28H43OH</chform>) found in foods such as milk and fish liver
oils. It is used as a dietary supplement in milk.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> vitamin D, ergocalciferol, cholecarciferol,
D.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>calciferous</ent>⟦br⟧
